Devon Energy production surge helps Q1 net . Devon Energy Corp said Monday that sharply higher oil , natural gas and natural gas liquids production helped earnings and revenues climb to record levels in the first quarter ended March 31 . The company said net income totaled $ 25 . 2 million , or $ 0 . 78 a share , compared with $ 5 . 6 million , or $ 0 . 25 , in the same period a year ago . Total revenues reached $ 87 . 9 million , versus $ 16 . 1 million in the first quarter of 1996 , Devon said . Devon said total production increased 91 percent to 4 . 96 million barrels of oil equivalent . Much of the production increase stemmed from the acquisition of oil and gas exploration and production assets of Kerr - McGee Corp in a deal that closed December 31 , Devon said . Devon is an independent energy company . Its shares were up 5 / 8 Monday at 29 - 1 / 4 . ( ( Chicago newsdesk ( 312 ) 408 - 8787 ) ) 
